"Velázquez A., Durán E., Ramírez I., Mas J.-F., Bocco G., Ramírez G., Palacio J.-L.","Land use-cover change processes in highly biodiverse areas: The case of Oaxaca, Mexico",2003,"Global Environmental Change","13","3",,"175","184",,,10.1016/S0959-3780(03)00035-9,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0042285801&partnerID=40&md5=e1fdd795548a67272f85c7d4ecd6d765","Instituto de Geografia, UNAM, Ciudad Universitaria, CP 04510, México DF, Mexico; Ctro. de Invest. en Ecosistemas, UNAM, Sucursal 3, Xangari, 58089 Morelia, Michoacan, Mexico; Centro, Calle Aquiles Serdan No. 382, CP 58000, Morelia, Michoacan, Mexico; Reforma Agraria 400-10, Morelia 58341, Michoacan, Mexico","Velázquez, A., Instituto de Geografia, UNAM, Ciudad Universitaria, CP 04510, México DF, Mexico, Centro, Calle Aquiles Serdan No. 382, CP 58000, Morelia, Michoacan, Mexico, Reforma Agraria 400-10, Morelia 58341, Michoacan, Mexico; Durán, E., Instituto de Geografia, UNAM, Ciudad Universitaria, CP 04510, México DF, Mexico; Ramírez, I., Instituto de Geografia, UNAM, Ciudad Universitaria, CP 04510, México DF, Mexico; Mas, J.-F., Instituto de Geografia, UNAM, Ciudad Universitaria, CP 04510, México DF, Mexico; Bocco, G., Ctro. de Invest. en Ecosistemas, UNAM, Sucursal 3, Xangari, 58089 Morelia, Michoacan, Mexico; Ramírez, G., Instituto de Geografia, UNAM, Ciudad Universitaria, CP 04510, México DF, Mexico; Palacio, J.-L., Instituto de Geografia, UNAM, Ciudad Universitaria, CP 04510, México DF, Mexico","Land use-cover changes (LUCC) such as deforestation, have resulted as global warming and a reduction of environmental services, with large negative consequences for mankind. Effects based on statistics alone have not been sufficient enough to detect, stop and eventually revert negative LUCC processes that are strongly related to biodiversity loss. It is, therefore, of prime concern to assess and depict cartographically, major LUCC processes simultaneously. Mexico harbors a large pool of biodiversity, mostly restricted to a few locations among which, The State of Oaxaca plays a major role. In this state, nevertheless, drastic negative LUCC processes are taking place. Land cover types, mapped in previous surveys, overlaid on recent Landsat imagery and 300 ground truth sites, were used to detect current LUCC. Rates of conversion of the most important LUCC processes were computed and mapped simultaneously. Oaxaca has lost over half a million hectares of forested areas during the last 20 years. The core results may contribute to the understanding of how LUCC and GIS methods can provide better and more targeted information that may help to improve conservation policies and land use planning strategies. © 2003 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.","Deforestation; GIS; Mexico; Oaxaca; Re-vegetation; Vegetation mapping","biodiversity; deforestation; environmental management; land use change; land use planning; Landsat; Mexico",,,,,,"Bocco, G., Velázquez, A., Torres, A., Comunidades indígenas y manejo de recursos naturales un caso de investigación participativa en México (2000) Interciencia, 25, pp. 9-19; Boege, E., (2001) Protegiendo lo Nuestro, , CONABIO-UNAM, México, DF; Bray, B.D., Merino-Pérez, L., Barry, D., (2003) The Community-Managed Forests of Mexico: The Struggle for Sustainability and Equity, , Florida University Press, Florida. In press; Constanza, R., Darge, R., Degroot, R., Farber, S., Grasso, M., Hannon, B., Limburg, K., Vandenbelt, M., The value of the world's ecosystem services and natural capital (1997) Nature, 387, pp. 253-260; Daily, G.C., Alexander, S., Ehrlich, P.R., Goulder, L., Lubchenco, J., Matson, P.A., Mooney, H.A., Woodwell, G.M., Ecosystems services: Benefits supplied to human societies by natural ecosystems (1996) Issues in Ecology, 2, pp. 1-16; (1996) Forest Resources Assessment 1990. Survey of Tropical Forest Cover and Study of Change Processes, , Number 130, Rome; Global forest resources assessment 2000 (2001) FAO Forestry Paper, 140. , Main report, Rome; Fearnside, M.P., Saving tropical forests as a global warming countermeasure: An issue that divides the environmental movement (2001) Ecological Economics, 39, pp. 167-184; Groombridge, B., Jenkins, M.D., (2000) Global Biodiversity. Earth's Living Resources in the 21st Century, , IUCN, Gland, Switzerland; García, G.G., March, I., Castillo, M., Transformación de la vegetación por cambio de uso del suelo en la Reserva de la Biosfera Calakmul, Campeche (2002) Investigaciones Geográficas (UNAM), 46, pp. 45-57; Gerez, P., Flores, O., (1994) Biodiversidad y Conservación en México: Vertebrados Vegetación y uso del Suelo, , Facultad de Ciencias, Mexico, DF; Klooster, D., Masera, O., Community forest management in Mexico: Carbon mitigation and biodiversity conservation through rural development (2000) Global Environmental Change, 10, pp. 259-272; Lambin, E.F., Turner, B.L., Helmut, J., Geist, S.B., Agbola, S.B., Arild, A., Bruce, J.W., Xu, C.J., The causes of land-use and land-cover change: Moving beyond the myths (2001) Global Environmental Change, 11, pp. 261-269; López, E., (2003) Land Use/cover Change in Cuitzeo, , Ph.D. Dissertation. UNAM, Mexico; Lorence, D.H., García, A., Oaxaca, Mexico (1989) Floristic Inventory of Tropical Countries, , Campbell, D.G., Hammond, H.D. (Eds.). NewYork Botanical Garden Pub, Bronx; Mas, J.F., Velásquez, A., Palacio-Prieto, J.L., Bocco, G., Peralta, A., Prado, J., Assessing forest resources in Mexico: Wall-to-wall land use/cover mapping (2002) Photogrametric Engineering and Remote Sensing, 2002, pp. 966-968; Mas, J.F., Velázquez, A., Palacio-Prieto, J.L., Bocco, G., (2003) Elaboración de Una Base de Datos Geográfica Sobre Recursos Forestales: El Inventario Forestal Nacional 2001-2001 de México, , Quebracho. In press; Miranda, F., Hernández, E., Los tipos de vegetación de México y su clasificación (1963) Boletín de la Sociedad Botánica de México, 28, pp. 29-179; Mittermeier, R.A., Primate diversity and the tropical forest. C